Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

While the rice cooks, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and fry until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the garlic and @Central American style spice mix{1%sachet} to the beef. Stir-fry until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Pour the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @chicken stock paste{10%g} and the @water for the sauce{150%ml} into the pan. Add a pinch of @?sugar{pinch}. Stir together and bring to the boil, then reduce the heat.

Simmer, stirring occasionally, until the sauce has thickened, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then remove from the heat.

Meanwhile, cut the @medium tomatoes{2}(cut into 1cm chunks) into pieces. Pop the tomato chunks into a #small bowl{} with the @olive oil for the salsa{1%tbsp}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, mix together, then set your salsa aside.

Grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{30%g}(grated).

When everything's ready, fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the beef chilli, tomato salsa and grated Cheddar in separate sections over the rice, then add a dollop of @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g}.

Finish with a sprinkle of @chilli flakes{pinch} for those who'd like some more heat (add less if you'd prefer things milder). Enjoy!